result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandon Debuhr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant is NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration and Substance Abuse Programs. Sentence credit of 2 days were granted if imposed.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid as a condition of probation.
Register as a Sex Offender with the Sex Offender registry. Comply with Sex offender treatment. Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by agent.

No unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18 yrs unless approved by agent. No Contact with the victim or her family or her residence. Provide DNA Specimen unless previously obtained. Surcharge is imposed. Maintain employment and/or school combination. Obtain his HSED or GED. Case 14CF997 was dismissed and read in.
  If Probation/Extended Supervision is revoked and/or a prison term ordered, outstanding financial obligations shall be collected pursuant to statutory provisions, including deductions from inmate prison monies.  If discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collections may include income assignment.

Defendant Brandon  Debuhr in court with Attorney Katie B. Bricco.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called for sentencing hearing.  Dawn M. makes statements.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Bricco makes statements regarding sentencing.  Gary D. makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

5  YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 2 days)
  -  2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISON 

TERM OF PROBATION:   5 YEARS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____Register as a Sex Offender with Sex Offender registry
____Sex Offender treatment
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling-obtain HSED/GED 
____No contact with:  victim or her family or her residence 
____No unsupervised contact with: anyone under 18 unless approved by agent
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

COSTS:  $268.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a conditions of probation)  

CONDITION TIME:  10 months,  Non-working hours with standard release conditions to commence forthwith.  Defendant taken into custody. 

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
